250px|thumb|the circassian flag the circassians ( circassian : адыгэхэр , adygekher ) are a north caucasian ethnic group native to circassia , who were displaced in the course of the russian conquest of the caucasus in the 19th century , especially after the russian–circassian war in 1864 .

people & places : the circassians are among the many peoples of this region , kavkaz in russian

